Brazilian Stock Movers: Comgas Advances; Gafisa and Vale Tumble

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-10-20T20:30:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/brazilian-stock-movers-comgas-eternit-advance-vale-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index tumbled 1.7 percent to 54,009.98.  Cia. de Gas de Sao Paulo (CGAS5 BS) rose 3.1 percent to
35.35 reais, the highest price since Sept. 16.  Brazil ’s biggest
gas distributor, known as Comgas, said in a regulatory filing it
will study the possibility of joining BM&FBovespa SA’s Novo
Mercado segment, which requires all shares to have  voting
rights .  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS) tumbled 5.2 percent to 5.83 reais. The
stock retreated from a one-month high as homebuilders declined
after traders pared bets for lower borrowing costs in Brazil.
The central bank yesterday cut the benchmark rate by a half
percentage point, quelling speculation it would accelerate the
pace of cuts.  Lupatech SA (LUPA3)  (LUPA3 BS) dropped 2 percent to 7.84 reais.
Brazil’s largest oil equipment and services provider was
downgraded to Caa2 from Caa1 by Moody’s Investors Service.  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) declined 1.3 percent to 37.21 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer dropped for a second day amid
concern declines in the price for the steelmaking ingredient may
deepen as  China’s economy  slows and the European debt crisis
persists.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
